A:
Let the age of the youngest member = x. Then, the age of the oldest member = (250 - x). Hence, (250 - x) - (x) = 3 months. Sub, (250 - x) = 3 * (x + 1) So, 250 - x = 3 * (x + 1) Sub, 250 - x = 3 * (x + 1) - 3 x = 3 * (x + 1) - 3 x = 3 * (x + 1) - 3 = 3 * (x + 1) - 3 = 3 * (x + 1) = 9. So, x = 9. Hence, the number of members in the club are 27. So, the answer is (e).

